#langchain-community -- is  used to load documents from various sources, including text files and PDFs. It provides a unified interface for loading documents, making it easier to work with different types of data sources. 
#The library includes various document loaders, such as TextLoader for loading text files and PyPDFLoader or PyMuPDFLoader for loading PDF files.


#pypdf
#pymupdf. These are the two libraries that are used to load PDF files. You can choose either of them based on your preference and requirements.

# embeddings = convert text into vector representations,
# sentence-transformers -- this library is used to generate embeddings for the documents. It provides pre-trained models that can be used to convert text into vector representations, which can then be stored in a vector database for efficient retrieval.


